parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the taillights can lead to a safety hazard, as it may cause accidents or leave the driver stranded, and may result in traffic violations.
symptoms: The taillights are inoperable
the brake lights are intermittently inoperable
the taillights flicker
the taillights do not work at all
the brake lights do not work at all.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake lights can lead to accidents or near-misses, as other drivers may not be aware of the vehicle's intention to stop.
symptoms: Intermittent or complete failure of the brake lights
including the LED lights on the rear of the vehicle.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the clutch hydraulic system can cause the clutch pedal to stick to the floor, making it difficult or impossible to shift gears, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The clutch pedal feels soft or spongy
the clutch pedal sticks to the floor
the clutch pedal does not return to its normal position
the clutch pedal has a delayed return to its normal position
the clutch pedal has a sudden loss of pressure
the vehicle is unable to shift into gear.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the engine coolant temperature sensor can cause the electric cooling fans to turn on at full speed, depleting the battery and potentially leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The engine temperature gauge does not work
the electric cooling fans turn on at full speed
the battery is depleted.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the trailer brake system can cause the brakes to not engage, leading to accidents or near-misses.
symptoms: The trailer brake system warning light comes on
the brakes do not engage
the warning chime sounds repeatedly.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Water ingress can cause electrical failures and shortages, leading to malfunctions of various systems.
